accessibility.text: no convergence and well-defined onlap - Cb
Linked salt-withdrawal intraslope basins receiving sediment from the Brazos and the Trinity Rivers
2 stratigraphic units bounded by condensed sections consist of turbidites and slump deposits over the last 16,000 yr.
strong convergence and poorly defined onlap - Ct
no bypass -> opportunity to understand how stratigraphic packages can develop in such settings.
Basin 4 is the deepest depression blocking all sediments
- Cst subsidence rate 0.1 mm/yr + sed. input x 25 btw phase 1 & 2
- Model captures well the key differences between the lower and upper stratigraphic packages
